posts.name: Joe Ross
posts.cooked: Those are really old software that isn’t compatible with the 2025 WPILib release (SparkMax-java is from 2021). You need to update your software to use 2025 libraries. The Vendor Dependency Manager makes it easy to find libraries compatible with 2025 WPILib

posts.name: Joe Ross
posts.cooked:
Your build.gradle has a ton of stuff manually defined in it, including manually setting up repositories, and manually adding the Spark Max version 1.5.3 library. Also your gradle version is 8.3, which was never a version used for gradlerio.

Since it doesn’t look like you’ve written much code, I recommend starting a new project following the directions at Creating a Robot Program — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation

What directions did you follow that got you to the state you are at? Something is really messed up. I’m also not sure where wpilib recommends installing all vendor libraries. Where did you find that?
